bib.title: Cross sections for proton induced reactions on K-41 and for the reaction Ni-62(alpha,p)29-Cu-65

free_txt: Pelletron accelerator

Statistical-model analysis. Thermonuclear

Pelletron accelerator
Private communication.
The 62Ni(alpha,p)65Cu cross sections were determined
relative to the Rutherford scattering cross section
over 6.5-8.5 MeV energy range. Above 8.5 MeV, where
the Rutherford law was not followed, the excitation
function was measured relative to the charge
collected in a Faraday cup located behind the target,
and normalized to the measurements made below 8.5 MeV.
/By compiler/ Cross section for (alpha,p(0)) is very
close to total cross-section.
Systematic error
Statistical error
A thin self-supporting target was
prepared by evaporation of nickel metal,enriched to
96.64% in Ni-62, from a tungsten boat on to a glass
slide coated with potassium iodide as a release agent.

A target was prepared by
evaporation of KBr, enriched to 99.35% in K-41,on to a
gold backing of supporting thickness. The adopted value
for the KBr target was (1.08+-0.07) x 1O**18 atoms/cm2
of 41K.
/By authors/ The K-41(p,alpha(0))Ar-38 alpha-particles
were separated from the high flux of protons,
elastically scattered mainly by the gold target
backing, by means of a permanent magnet with a field
of 10E+4 G between its pole faces, and detected by a
16 mm diameter surface barrier detector.
/by compiler/ Total cross section is very close to
this partial cross section.
